      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/38/11",
      "text": [
        ": «إِذَا اِعْتَكَفَ اَلرَّجُلُ يَوْماً وَ لَمْ يَكُنِ اِشْتَرَطَ فَلَهُ أَنْ يَخْرُجَ وَ أَنْ يَفْسَخَ اِعْتِكَافَهُ وَ إِنْ أَقَامَ يَوْمَيْنِ وَ لَمْ يَكُنِ اِشْتَرَطَ فَلَيْسَ لَهُ أَنْ يَفْسَخَ اِعْتِكَافَهُ حَتَّى تَمْضِيَ ثَلاَثَةُ أَيَّامٍ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2096 - It is narrated by Abu Ayyub, from Muhammad ibn Muslim, from Abu Ja'far (as), who said:\n\"If a man begins i'tikaf for one day and has not made any stipulation, he is allowed to leave and break his i'tikaf. However, if he has completed two days without making a stipulation, he is not permitted to break his i'tikaf until three days have been completed.\""
        ]
      }
    },
